<dl id="s14009k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14009k">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s14all.htm#s14009k">sector 9(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> a 2 or 3 months, ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> The archbishop of Canterbury, who was informed of the saying of this John Ball, caused him to be taken and put in prison <mark>a two or three months</mark> to chastise him <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> but the bishop had conscience to <font color="green">[was morally unprepared to]</font> let him die. <small> William Peacock, <a name="WPEP" href="/udra/udex.htm#WPEP"><cite title="source">English Prose from Mandeville to Ruskin</cite></a> (1903), 15, Berners</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
